<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Data Generator Architecture · Bida Platform</title>
    <link
        href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
        rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/animate.css/4.1.1/animate.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/theme.css">
    <script type="module">
        import mermaid from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@10/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs';
        mermaid.initialize({
            startOnLoad: true,
            theme: 'base',
            themeVariables: {
                darkMode: true,
                primaryColor: 'rgba(0, 237, 100, 0.1)',
                primaryTextColor: '#00ED64',
                primaryBorderColor: '#00ED64',
                lineColor: '#3B82F6',
                secondaryColor: '#001E2B',
                tertiaryColor: '#1C2D38'
            }
        });
    </script>
    <style>
        :root {
            --mongo-green: #00ed64;
            --mongo-dark: #001e2b;
            --bg-dark: #020617;
            --glass-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
            --glass-bg: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.85);
            --text-primary: #FFFFFF;
            --text-secondary: #E2E8F0;
            --accent-blue: #3b82f6;
            --accent-purple: #8b5cf6;
            --code-bg: #0d1117;
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            scroll-behavior: smooth;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            color: var(--text-primary);
            line-height: 1.8;
            overflow-x: hidden;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1100px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 1.5rem 8rem;
        }

        /* --- Header --- */
        .doc-header {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 8rem 1rem 5rem;
            position: relative;
        }

        .doc-header::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            width: 200px;
            height: 1px;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--mongo-green), transparent);
        }

        .badge {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            color: var(--mongo-green);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;
            border: 1px solid rgba(0, 237, 100, 0.2);
            border-radius: 50px;
            background: rgba(0, 237, 100, 0.05);
            display: inline-block;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        .doc-title {
            font-size: 3.5rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 30%, #94a3b8 100%);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }

        .doc-subtitle {
            font-size: 1.25rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            font-weight: 300;
            max-width: 700px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        /* --- Glass Cards --- */
        .section {
            margin-bottom: 4rem;
            scroll-margin-top: 4rem;
        }

        .card {
            background: var(--glass-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 2.5rem;
            backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 1rem;
        }

        h2::before {
            content: '';
            width: 12px;
            height: 12px;
            background: var(--mongo-green);
            border-radius: 2px;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        h3 {
            font-size: 1.4rem;
            color: #fff;
            margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            color: #cbd5e1;
        }

        .code-block {
            background: #0d1117;
            border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 1.5rem 0;
            color: #e6edf3;
        }

        /* Mermaid Wrapper */
        .mermaid-card {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            padding: 2rem;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin: 2rem 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        /* --- Home Button --- */
        .home-btn {
            position: fixed;
            top: 2rem;
            left: 2rem;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.8);
            border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
            backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            z-index: 200;
            transition: all 0.2s;
        }

        .home-btn:hover {
            color: #fff;
            border-color: var(--mongo-green);
        }

        .feature-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
            gap: 1.5rem;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }

        .feature-item {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
            border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 12px;
        }

        .feature-item strong {
            color: var(--mongo-green);
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        /* Syntax colors */
        .k {
            color: #ff7b72;
        }

        .s {
            color: #a5d6ff;
        }

        .f {
            color: #d2a8ff;
        }

        .c {
            color: #8b949e;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Unified Background -->
    <div class="ambient-orb orb-1"></div>
    <div class="ambient-orb orb-2"></div>
    <div class="ambient-orb orb-3"></div>
    <canvas id="particle-canvas"></canvas>

    <a href="/" class="home-btn">← Query Lab</a>

    <div class="container animate__animated animate__fadeIn">

        <header class="doc-header">
            <div class="badge">Architecture Guide</div>
            <h1 class="doc-title">Data Generation Engine</h1>
            <p class="doc-subtitle">Inside the `generate_data.py` logic: How we seed the Bida Platform with realistic,
                interconnected educational datasets.</p>
        </header>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>1. Core Objectives</h2>
                <p>The <code>generate_data.py</code> script is responsible for building a production-grade synthetic
                    environment. Its goals are:</p>
                <div class="feature-grid">
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <strong>Relational Integrity</strong>
                        Maintaining strict Foreign Key-like links using MongoDB ObjectIds.
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <strong>BSON Compliance</strong>
                        Exporting data in Extended JSON format for seamless MongoDB importing.
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <strong>Realistic Entropy</strong>
                        Applying weighted probability for student enrollment statuses and grades.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>2. Data Workflow</h2>
                <p>The generation process follows a linear dependency chain to ensure that every Course has a Category,
                    and every Enrollment has both a Student and a Course.</p>

                <div class="mermaid-card">
                    <div class="mermaid">
                        graph TD
                        A[Start] --> B(Categories)
                        B --> C(Instructors)
                        C --> D(Students)
                        B & C --> E(Courses)
                        D & E --> F(Enrollments)
                        D & E --> G(Reviews)
                        D & E --> H(Payments)
                        F & G & H --> I[Export to Extended JSON]
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>3. Key Technologies</h2>
                <ul style="list-style: none;">
                    <li><strong>• Pymongo (json_util):</strong> Used to handle MongoDB-specific types
                        (<code>$oid</code>, <code>$date</code>) during serialization.</li>
                    <li><strong>• BSON:</strong> Native <code>ObjectId()</code> generation for realistic identifier
                        entropy.</li>
                    <li><strong>• Randomization:</strong> Weighted choice distributions for 'status' fields (92% Active,
                        8% Inactive).</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Implementation Snippet: ObjectId Generation</h3>
                <div class="code-block">
                    <span class="c"># Realistic ID linking strategy</span>
                    <span class="k">from</span> bson <span class="k">import</span> ObjectId, json_util

                    <span class="k">def</span> <span class="f">generate_student</span>():
                    <span class="k">return</span> {
                    <span class="s">"_id"</span>: <span class="f">ObjectId</span>(), <span class="c"># Binary
                        GUID</span>
                    <span class="s">"name"</span>: <span class="s">"Faker Name"</span>,
                    <span class="s">"status"</span>: <span class="s">"active"</span>
                    }
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>4. The Relational Model</h2>
                <p>Unlike standard Flat-JSON generation, the Bida Generator maintains a graph of dependencies:</p>

                <div class="feature-grid">
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <strong>Courses</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:0.85rem">Stores <code>category_id</code> and <code>instructor_id</code>.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <strong>Enrollments</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:0.85rem">Junction document mapping <code>student_id</code> to
                            <code>course_id</code>.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-item">
                        <strong>Analytics</strong>
                        <p style="font-size:0.85rem">Calculates <code>final_grade</code> based on
                            <code>status="completed"</code>.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="info-box tip"
                    style="padding: 1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--mongo-green); background: rgba(0, 237, 100, 0.05); border-radius: 8px;">
                    <strong>Design Choice: Extended JSON</strong>
                    <br>Standard JSON doesn't support Dates or ObjectIds. The script exports using
                    <code>json_util.dumps()</code> to ensure <code>{"$oid": "..."}</code> wrappers are present, allowing
                    <code>mongoimport</code> to recognize binary types.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-blue)">
                <h2>5. Scale Parameters</h2>
                <p>The current simulator configuration generates:</p>
                <div class="grid-2" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem;">
                    <div>
                        <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-secondary);">
                            <li>• Students: <strong>500</strong></li>
                            <li>• Courses: <strong>80</strong></li>
                            <li>• Instructors: <strong>15</strong></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-secondary);">
                            <li>• Enrollments: <strong>1,400</strong></li>
                            <li>• Reviews: <strong>900</strong></li>
                            <li>• Payments: <strong>1,200</strong></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>
    <script src="/js/background.js"></script>
</body>

</html>